# AGENTS â€” ROLES AND CAPABILITIES

PURPOSE:
  Define the canonical set of agent roles used by Life-OS.
  Make responsibilities, allowed actions, stop conditions, and escalation triggers explicit.

SCOPE:
  This file defines:
    - role definitions
    - authority boundaries (conceptual)
    - required inputs and allowed outputs
    - stop conditions and escalation triggers

  This file does NOT define:
    - per-role implementation
    - tool wiring (MCP, APIs)
    - storage layout
    - UI behavior

RULE:
  Roles describe capability intent.
  Contracts and permissions decide what can actually happen.

---

# ROLE FORMAT

ROLE_FIELDS:
  ROLE_NAME:
  PURPOSE:
  PRIMARY_RESPONSIBILITIES:
  ALLOWED_OUTPUTS:
  FORBIDDEN_ACTIONS:
  STOP_CONDITIONS:
  ESCALATION_TRIGGERS:
  REQUIRED_INPUTS:
  OPTIONAL_INPUTS:
  TAGS:

RULE:
  Any role may propose.
  No role may commit meaning unless explicitly authorized by COMMIT contracts.

